Thirty-two new cases of COVID-19 have been recorded in Kano State. The State Ministry of Health disclosed this on Tuesday. According to the Ministry, the State now has 397 confirmed cases and 8 deaths. It also stated that there are 386 active cases as three patients were discharged on Tuesday. “COVID19KN Update as at 11:55pm 5th May 2020 “ 32 new cases of #COVID19Kano cases confirmed. “Total confirmed cases in @KanostateNg are now 397. “ 3 #COVID19Kano patients were discharged. #StayAtHomeStaySafe #MaskUpKano #PrayForKano.”